The course provides an overview of the fundamentals of self-management and teaches practical skills in the following areas: setting development tasks and aiming for action, finding and overcoming personal constraints in professional development, analysing and planning personal professional development, using time efficiently, managing emotions, coping with stress and preventing burnout.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at supporting the self-guided learning and development process of students by helping them to become aware of their personal resources and limitations in the fields related to learning and professional development, also by developing self-regulation and time-management skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) analyse their responsibility in the learning process; 2) analyse their strengths and limitations as learners and rely on them in the learning process and in professional development; 3) analyse their use of time in the learning process; 4) know the symptoms of stress and ways of preventing stress; 5) create opportunities to cope with internal and external factors affecting the learning process; 6) instruct group work, conduct a seminar, and receive and provide feedback on the teaching process; 7)  set themselves objectives and motivate themselves to overcome the obstacles to achieving their objectives.
